# IncentiveDrive — Daily Incentive Refresh Cron Jobs
#
# Setup instructions:
#   1. Copy this file or install entries into your crontab:
#        crontab -e
#   2. Replace /path/to/car-incentive with the actual project root.
#   3. Ensure python3 points to the correct virtualenv or use the full
#      path to the venv Python binary (e.g., /path/to/venv/bin/python3).
#   4. Create the log directory if it does not exist:
#        sudo mkdir -p /var/log && sudo touch /var/log/incentive-refresh.log /var/log/oem-monitor.log
#   5. Make sure the cron user has write access to the log files.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Job 1: MarketCheck incentive data refresh
#
# Pulls the latest vehicle pricing and inventory data from the MarketCheck
# API and refreshes the local incentive cache. Runs once daily at 5:00 AM
# UTC, before the OEM monitor jobs, so downstream tasks operate on fresh
# baseline data.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
0 5 * * * cd /path/to/car-incentive/apps/api && python3 -m app.tasks.refresh_incentives >> /var/log/incentive-refresh.log 2>&1

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Jobs 2 & 3: OEM Incentive Monitor (split into two batches)
#
# The OEM monitor scrapes official manufacturer incentive pages using
# Google Gemini for extraction. The work is split into two batches to
# stay within the Gemini free-tier rate limits:
#
#   Batch A (6:00 AM UTC) — Acura through Honda
#   Batch B (6:30 AM UTC) — Hyundai through Volvo
#
# The 30-minute gap between batches lets the Gemini rate-limit window
# reset, avoiding 429 errors that would cause missed updates.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
0 6 * * * cd /path/to/car-incentive/apps/api && python3 -m app.tasks.oem_incentive_monitor a >> /var/log/oem-monitor.log 2>&1
30 6 * * * cd /path/to/car-incentive/apps/api && python3 -m app.tasks.oem_incentive_monitor b >> /var/log/oem-monitor.log 2>&1
